```

We are developing a MMORPG which involving large number of players with difference outfit (texture) in the same screen. We are using csb animations, Since TextureFrame doesn't hold the reference of SpriteFrame, then SpriteFrameCache::removeUnusedSpriteFrames will simply cleanup all caches, and the running TextureFrame lost its texture ( failed to load form SpriteFrameCache) .

cocos2d::Map may cause Dangling Pointers when inserting Ref Object which already exist
CCMap  line 274

``` C++
    void insert(const K& key, V object)
    {
        CCASSERT(object != nullptr, "Object is nullptr!");
        erase(key);
        _data.insert(std::make_pair(key, object));
        object->retain();
    }
```

For example
Object A already exist in Map B, and Map B has the very last reference of Object A. The code above will release Object A and Object A will be deleted, then Map B holds a Dangling Pointer.

How about retain the input object first, or check if the input object exist?

